## Variants

### Variant A: AIMS-bridged meeting (Aramco / ADNOC / Q-Chem / etc.)

- **To**: AIMS attendees + customer attendees (per the meeting attendee list)
- **CC**: SRE internal stakeholders not in the meeting
- Lead with thanks to both AIMS and customer side
- Action items should clearly distinguish SRE-owned vs AIMS-owned vs customer-owned

### Variant B: Internal SRE meeting (Bi-Weekly Job, Pit Stop, etc.)

- **To**: SRE attendees only
- **CC**: Operator (for record)
- Drop signature block; just "Maaz"
- Tone shifts from "Best regards" to "Thanks" — internal
- Action items typically smaller scope (project-level, not customer-level)

### Variant C: One-on-one (Maaz × Ron, Maaz × Torstein, Maaz × Ashley)

- Skip the formal recap entirely if both parties already capture in their own logs
- Use this template only if there were ≥ 3 distinct decisions/actions
- **To**: the 1:1 partner only
- Drop the table; use bullets

### Variant D: Confidential meeting (sale-process, Torstein 1:1, board prep)

- **STOP. Don't use this skill.** Sale-process recaps need a different (manual) workflow because the recap itself is confidential. Notes go to operator-private file, not email.
